course_name: Adolescent Gang Intervention
description: The incidence of gangs (particularly in the Los Angeles area), gang interventions, and policies developed to address the growing gang situation.

course_name: Special Problems
description: Supervised, individual studies. No more than one registration permitted. Enrollment by petition only.

course_name: Introduction to Substance Use Disorders and Recovery
description: Social work approach to understanding substance misuse and other addictive behaviors.

course_name: Community Experience in Juvenile Justice Environments
description: Provides in-class and on-site community experiences to increase knowledge and understanding of youth experience in a range of social environments focused on juvenile justice.

course_name: Human Behavior and the Social Environment
description: The person-in-environment, bio-psycho-social perspective is the lens through which theories of personality, family, group, organization, community, culture and their interactions are explored. (Duplicates credit in SOWK 503 and SOWK 505)

course_name: Interprofessional Education and Collaboration for Geriatrics
description: Students from multiple health professions learn about aging and collaborative team care through a combination of didactic and experiential learning working in a community-based setting.

course_name: Professional Self-Care in Integrative Social Work Practice
description: Focuses on the value, examination and integration of professional self-care, wellness and resilience strategies into ethical and professional integrative social work practice.

course_name: Foundations of Integrative Social Work Practice I
description: Principles underlying social work practice with emphasis on rapport building, engagement, assessment and contracting individuals, families and groups though a framework of social justice.

course_name: Foundations of Integrative Social Work Practice II
description: Principles underlying social work practice with emphasis on intervention, termination and evaluation with individuals, families and groups though a framework of social justice

course_name: Directed Research
description: Research leading to the master's degree. Maximum units which may be applied to the degree to be determined by the department. Graded CR/NC.

course_name: Applied Learning in Practicum Education I
description: Supervised beginning generalist practicum seminar and placement to develop practice skills in working with individuals, families, groups, communities and/or organizations.

course_name: Applied Learning in Practicum Education II
description: Supervised generalist master's level practicum seminar and placement to develop practice skills in working with individuals, families, groups, communities and/or organizations.

course_name: Social Work Perspectives on Contemporary Challenges in Educa
description: Provides a holistic understanding of the current issues students and their families must confront. Explores interventions grounded in evidence, best practice models, strength-based and asset-driven.

course_name: Research and Evaluation in Integrative Social Work Practice
description: Critical analysis and application of empirical evidence and research methods to assess client strengths and needs and to evaluate and improve integrative social work practice.

course_name: Assessment and Diagnosis of Mental Disorders
description: Assessment of mental disorders, and the rationale and organization of the system for diagnosis. Emphasis is on developing differential diagnostic skills.

course_name: Social Work Practice in School Settings
description: Based on ecosystems perspectives, this course examines policies, theories and principles for social work practice in school settings.

course_name: Substance Related and Behavioral Addictive Disorders and Rec
description: Causal exploration of substance related and behavioral addictive disorders. Evidence-based and practice informed treatment models for vulnerable individuals, groups and families.

course_name: Social Work in Public Child Welfare Settings
description: Provides tools to enhance the practitioner's repsonse ot the special challenges (substance abuse, HIV/AIDS, domestic violence) in public child welfare.

course_name: Practice and Policy with Children and Families Across Settings
description: Provides context and preparation for integrative social work practitioners on organizational and policy practice, and leadership in communities and systems serving children, youth and families.

course_name: Visual Social Work
description: Explores a method of social work practice that reviews the dominant role of visual input in the way we assess, intervene and evaluate in social work practice.

course_name: Diversity, Social Justice and Interculturally Competent Soci
description: Introduction to diversity and social justice in the context of social work practice. Enhance intercultural competence by raising awareness of one's own values/assumptions/biases.

course_name: Life in the US Military: Foundations of Practice in Military
description: Examines the experience of military service, including challenges and theoretical and empirical foundations of military social work clinical practice.

course_name: Policy Advocacy and Social Change
description: Analysis of efforts to improve local human services organizations and agencies with consideration of political, social, demographic and organization contexts. Prerequisite: SOWK 506, SOWK 536, SOWK 544, SOWK 546.

course_name: Social Work Practice in Integrated Care Settings
description: Social work processes and skills required for the implementation of short-term interventions in medical, behavioral health and integrated care settings with individuals, families and groups.

course_name: Clinical Psychopharmacology for Social Workers
description: Understanding major psychoactive drugs used in treatment of psychological and behavioral disorders in behavioral and primary care medical settings. Theoretical/practical approaches to treatment are examined.

course_name: Interprofessional Education, Team-Based Care and Caregivers
description: Interprofessional education and evidence-informed team-based practice revolving around formal and informal caregiving through a social justice and intercultural competence lens.

course_name: Telebehavioral Health Practice
description: Essential legal, ethical and practice competencies of providing telebehavioral health services

course_name: Grant Writing and Program Development for Social Workers
description: Grant writing and program development that are generalized to any settings and relevant to direct and macro social work practice expertise.

course_name: Mental Health Assessment and Diagnosis of Children and Adole
description: Mental health assessment and diagnosis of children and adolescents. Course includes relevant diagnoses and the systematic or societal challenges that impact mental health of youth.

course_name: Applied Learning In Practicum Education III
description: Supervised practicum seminar and placement to develop practice skills in working with individuals, families, groups, communities and/or organizations.

course_name: Advanced Clinical Social Work Practice Certificate Lab
description: Clinical practice lab designed to strengthen clinical social work practice skills grounded in professional values and ethics.

course_name: Theories of Human Behavior in the Contexts of Social Environments
description: A focus on human behavior in interaction with the social environment; major paradigms including general systems theory, ego psychology, and role theories are examined.

course_name: Explanatory Theories for Larger Social Systems
description: Theories of organizational and community behavior are examined in relation to their influence on the development of social services.

course_name: Introductory Social Work Statistics
description: Foundation course covering univariate and bivariate descriptive and inferential statistics. Required lab covering basic computer skills and utilization of statistical software.

course_name: Social Work Research Methods I
description: Models of research, the ;nature of inquiry, and the research process including problem formulation, measurement, designs, sampling and data sources. Doctoral standing required.

course_name: Advanced Multivariate Statistics
description: Introduction to single equation statistical modeling using limited dependent variables (categorical and ordered categorical). Methods are drawn from statistics and econometrics.

course_name: Research
description: Research leading to the doctorate. Maximum units which may be applied to the degree to be determined by the department. Graded CR/NC.

description: Credit on acceptance of dissertation.
